The paper focuses on information retrieval evaluation and relevance assessments, which are key topics in the field of information retrieval (cs.IR). The fact that the study was conducted with LIS (Library and Information Science) students suggests a potential connection to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and education technology (cs.EDU). Additionally, the use of statistical measures such as Kappa and Alpha suggests a potential connection to natural language processing and machine learning (cs.CL, cs.DL).
